            <div type="translation" xml:lang="en" resp="#AA">
                <p>To Jupiter the Best and Greatest. For the safety of Caius Caesar Augustus Germanicus, imperator, pontifex maximus, with tribunician power, consul. [---] Doctus [made this] with his own money.</p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>The editors of the EpRom project propose to restore the name in line 5 as C. Fundilius Doctus, attested at Aricia (CIL 14.4199–4200) and Nemi (CIL 14.4273), and also suggest that the inscription could be linked to the illness that affected Caligula in the autumn of 37 CE (Suet. Cal. 14.2, 27.2).</p> 
            </div>
